TASK:
The four values must be printed on a single line in the order specified above for each i from n to numbers . Each value should 
be space-padded to match the width of the binary value of number and the values should be separated by a single space.
PROGRAM:
def print_formatted(number):
    width = len(bin(number)[2:])
    for i in range(1, number + 1):
        decimal = str(i)
        octal = oct(i)[2:]
        # 'X' for uppercase hexadecimal
        hexadecimal = hex(i)[2:].upper() 
        binary = bin(i)[2:]
        
        print(f"{decimal.rjust(width)} {octal.rjust(width)} {hexadecimal.rjust(width)} {binary.rjust(width)}")
if __name__ == '__main__':
        n = int(input())
        print_formatted(n)
